{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772647457,"nonce":"yj0xeVGdsHuXCEr9pTg3r1COvao=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vz3DC","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/349","origin":"github"},"title":"setup.bash does not source layers from layer worktree","message":"## Problem\n\n`setup.bash` does not source ROS 2 layers from the worktree's directory when called from a layer worktree. Instead, it always sources from `layers/main/`, ignoring the worktree's local `install/` for the modified layer.\n\n### Root cause\n\n`worktree_enter.sh` (line 270) sources `setup.bash` via absolute path:\n\n```bash\nsource \"$ROOT_DIR/.agent/scripts/setup.bash\"\n```\n\nInside `setup.bash`, `ROOT_DIR` is recalculated from `${BASH_SOURCE[0]}` (lines 22-23), which resolves back to the main workspace root (`/path/to/project11`). The worktree detection check (line 31) then fails because the path doesn't contain `/layers/worktrees/`:\n\n```bash\nif [[ \"$ROOT_DIR\" == *\"/layers/worktrees/\"* ]]; then  # never true\n```\n\nSo `LAYERS_BASE` defaults to `layers/main/` and the worktree's local build artifacts are never sourced.\n\n### Impact\n\n- Packages built locally in a layer worktree (e.g., `platforms_ws/install/`) are **not on the overlay path** — the main tree's stale build is sourced instead.\n- Non-modified layers (symlinked to main) work correctly by accident, since both paths resolve to the same place.\n- Agents must manually source the worktree's `install/setup.bash` to get their local build, defeating the purpose of worktree isolation.\n\n### Observed during\n\nTesting [ben_description PR #10](https://github.com/rolker/ben_description/pull/10) from its layer worktree — `ros2 launch -g` was unavailable because `setup.bash` wasn't sourcing the underlay properly, and the worktree-built `ben_description` wasn't on the path.\n\n### Suggested fix\n\nHave `worktree_enter.sh` export `ROS2_LAYERS_BASE` pointing to the worktree directory before sourcing `setup.bash`, and have `setup.bash` respect it if already set:\n\n```bash\n# In worktree_enter.sh, before sourcing setup.bash:\nexport ROS2_LAYERS_BASE=\"$WORKTREE_DIR\"\n\n# In setup.bash, at line 27:\nLAYERS_BASE=\"${ROS2_LAYERS_BASE:-$ROOT_DIR/layers/main}\"\n```\n\nThis keeps the existing detection logic as a fallback while allowing the caller to override.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}